   Welcome to Barbering and Cosmetology On-line Licensing System

   The On-line Professional Licensing System is available for Barber,
   Barber Instructor, Cosmetologist, Cosmetology Instructor,
   Electrologist, Esthetician, and Manicurist applicants and licensees.
   This system enables users to apply for licenses, renew licenses,
   request duplicate licenses, and make address changes. (Pre-applications
   are not available on-line at this time.)

   You are eligible to apply for the licensing examination online if:
     * You were trained in an approved California School or (Proof of
       Training must be mailed to the Bureau at P.O. Box 989051,
       Sacramento, CA 95798-9051 in an envelope marked On-line
       Transaction)
                                                                   or
       You have Out-of-State/Country training and/or experience. (Required
       forms are available at www.dca.ca.gov/barber and must be mailed to
       P.O. Box 989051, West Sacramento, CA 95798-9051, in an envelope
       marked On-line Transaction
                                                                   and
     * You have no outstanding fines with the Bureau of Barbering and
       Cosmetology.

              The following credit cards are accepted:
               VISA, MASTERCARD, DISCOVER
        ** There is a $2.00 convenience fee added to all on-line
   transactions that require a payment.

   You are eligible to renew online if:
     * You have a valid license that expires within the next 3 months or
     * You have a license that is delinquent by no more than 2 years and
     * You have no outstanding or disciplinary actions.

   FIRST TIME USERS -  You will need your:
     * Social Security Number
     * Credit Card Information
     * License number if you are renewing   -   Example (alpha/numeric =
       KB12345, KK12345)
     * eMail Address   -   Very important that you enter a correct email
       address   - Example ( jsmith@aaa.com )
     * Click here to get started, or click on Professional Licensing link
       in left column.

   RETURNING USERS -  You will need your:
     * User ID
     * Password
     * Credit Card Information
     * Click here to get started, or click on Professional Licensing link
       in left column.

   For assistance in the on-line process you may contact the Department of
   Consumer Affairs eGovernment Team at (916) 322-7834 between the hours
   of 8-5 PST Monday through Friday, or email to egov@dca.ca.gov.
   For licensing information you may contact the Bureau of Barbering and
   Cosmetology at (916) 445-0916.
   If you are a AOL user please read AOL User Browser Requirements here or
   on left menu bar.


